Troops of the Operation Lafiya Dole in Borno State have destroyed a training ground of Boko Haram militants in Kaga Local Government Area. They have also killed one Boko Haram fighter in a crossfire while an elderly man was rescued from captivity. Army Spokesman at the Theatre Command in Maiduguri, Col. Onyema Nwachukwu, said in a statement yesterday that following a tip-off on Sunday morning troops deployed at a Forward Operational Base in Benisheikh town uncovered a Boko Haram camp at Afa general area where insurgents were being trained. “Troops immediately mobilised to the area to confront elements of Boko Haram insurgents who were withdrawing hastily from the camp. In the shootout that ensued, troops killed one of the insurgents and recovered one Dane gun. Troops also rescued one Mallam Abba, who was held hostage in the camp by the insurgents,” Onyema Nwachukwu said.